The paper deals with the analysis of multiuser detection in MIMO DS-CDMA channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance and complexity of different spreading schemes, which could fall under signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of the replica method for analysis is a statistical physics technique, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
